The StringTokenizer class is used to break a string into tokens. The nextToken() method returns the next token from the string. The hasMoreTokens() method returns true if there are more tokens in the string.
The code uses a while loop to iterate through the tokens in the string. For each token, it checks if the map already contains the token. If it does, it increments the count for that token. If it doesn't, it adds the token to the map with a count of 1.
This code is not the most efficient way to count the number of occurrences of each token in the string, but it is a simple and easy to understand solution.
